        {
          "type": "reasoning",
          "text": "Now I have the guidelines. Let me plan an interactive roadmap for learning full-stack TypeScript. This is a great fit for an interactive HTML widget with a stepper/progression approach.\n\nThe roadmap should cover:\n1. TypeScript fundamentals\n2. Frontend with TypeScript (React/Next.js)\n3. Backend with TypeScript (Node.js)\n4. Database & ORM\n5. Full-stack integration\n6. Deployment & DevOps\n\nI'll create an interactive widget with:\n- Phases/stages that users can click through\n- Each phase shows topics, resources, and estimated time\n- Progress tracking with visual indicators\n- Click-through detail panels\n\nLet me design this as a rich interactive HTML widget with multiple phases, each expandable, with visual progression indicators.\n\nI'll use a stepper-style layout with phases that users can click to expand, showing subtopics and key skills for each phase.\n\nLet me think about the layout:\n- A vertical timeline/roadmap with phases\n- Each phase has a circle indicator and a card\n- Clicking a phase expands it to show details\n- A progress bar or phase indicator at the top\n\nLet me build this out. I need to keep it within the widget constraints - no gradients, no shadows, use CSS variables, etc.\n\nI'll structure the roadmap into these phases:\n1. TypeScript core (types, interfaces, generics, utility types)\n2. Frontend foundations (React + TS, state management, routing)\n3. Backend foundations (Node.js + TS, Express/Fastify, REST APIs)\n4. Database layer (PostgreSQL, Prisma/Drizzle, migrations)\n5. Full-stack framework (Next.js, tRPC, auth)\n6. Testing & quality (Jest, Playwright, linting)\n7. Deployment & DevOps (Docker, CI/CD, monitoring)\n\nLet me create an interactive widget with these phases. I'll make it so clicking a phase expands the detail card, and there's a progress indicator.\n\nI need to be careful about the complexity - keep it rich but not overflowing. Let me use a vertical stepper with clickable phase cards.\n\nLet me code this up now.",
          "state": "done"
        },
